00:03:56.070 --> 00:04:02.690
The eyebrows are NOT one solid tone.

00:04:02.690 --> 00:04:15.070
Try to observe the eyebrows of whoever you
are drawing before shading them.

00:04:15.070 --> 00:04:26.500
The only exception is when heavy make up is
applied.....Maybe its Maybelline!

00:04:26.500 --> 00:04:32.210
Shading is ALWAYS dependant upon LIGHT!

00:04:32.210 --> 00:04:43.640
There are no universal rules to applying tones
to drawing.....because lighting conditions

00:04:43.640 --> 00:04:46.490
vary so much!

00:04:46.490 --> 00:04:48.400
REMEMBER THAT!

00:04:48.400 --> 00:04:56.020
In this case, the light came from above.

00:04:56.020 --> 00:05:01.730
This is most often the case.

00:05:01.730 --> 00:05:13.160
Notice the shadow that I am adding between
the brow and eye.

00:05:13.160 --> 00:05:25.540
When drawing a smiling face, the area UNDER
the eye is very important!

00:05:25.540 --> 00:05:36.970
The orbicularis oculi muscle (muscle around
eye) contracts...The eye is ball shaped.....thus

00:05:36.970 --> 00:05:50.300
"eyeball"....our shading has to show that
it is ROUNDED!The brush is a BIG help.

00:05:50.300 --> 00:05:58.810
It allows me to shade something delicately....which
is needed, when drawing skin.....I use bristle

00:05:58.810 --> 00:06:00.390
AND soft tipped brushes.... both give slightly
different effects.

00:06:00.390 --> 00:06:04.900
REMEMBER, when a person is smiling, you will
(usually) only see their top row of teeth.

00:06:04.900 --> 00:06:06.880
ALSO, notice the corners of the mouth.

00:06:06.880 --> 00:06:11.430
Notice that the two sides of the mouth are
shaded dark (because the teeth wrap around

00:06:11.430 --> 00:06:21.760
in a horseshoe shape).REMEMBER, when a person
is smiling, you will (usually) only see their

00:06:21.760 --> 00:06:22.760
top row of teeth.

00:06:22.760 --> 00:06:25.120
Everyones smile (the shape of their mouth
during a smile) is unique!

00:06:25.120 --> 00:06:26.120
OBSERVE OBSERVE OBSERVE!

00:06:26.120 --> 00:06:28.050
Draw in the lashes as triangular masses.

00:06:28.050 --> 00:06:31.919
Notice that the top eyelashes are a LOT longer
and fuller than the bottom lashes.

00:06:31.919 --> 00:06:32.919
This is the case for everybody.

00:06:32.919 --> 00:06:34.060
Males, in general have shorter lashes than
females...Maybe he's born with it...Maybe

00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:35.060
its TESTOSTERONE!

